line_1: His tongue was poisonous as an aspic's tooth.
line_2: His cheeks impurpled with the rose of youth;

line_1: His tongue was poisonous as an aspic's tooth.
line_2: They thought they listen'd to the words of truth,

line_1: His tongue was poisonous as an aspic's tooth.
line_2: Yet their belief did work them muchel ruth.
Or pining Love shall waste their youth,

line_1: Sprung from the dragon's venom'd tooth,
line_2: So when the fierce Cadmean youth
Nor fill our hearts with ruth;

line_1: But, O! you've lost a tooth.
line_2: In all the charms of youth;

line_1: To say she's lost a tooth.
Were all their loss a tooth!

line_2: Or pineing love shall waste their youth,

line_1: And break the Canker's desolating tooth.
line_2: Deep-rooted Mould, and Ergot's horn uncouth,
And Love, which feeds upon our youth,
One was to rough, t'other to smooth,
